Employee Plan. The options generally become exercisable to the extent of one-third of the optioned shares for each full year
following the date of grant and generally expire ten years after the date of grant. Unrecognized compensation expense with respect
to options granted to eligible employees amounted to $84.4 million at December 31, 2022. The unrecognized compensation
expense is being amortized on a straight-line basis over the three-year vesting period, net of estimated forfeitures based on
historical activity, and is expected to be recognized over a weighted-average period of 1.09 years.
